key-39-blue.def: MPAs can be more easily created by governments in national waters where there are dedicated legal systems in place. In ABNJ it is more difficult to create MPAs due to the complex legal framework in place. As such, the percentage of MPAs created within national waters is much higher than that for ABNJ. National waters represent 39% of the global ocean and at present, 17.86% of these waters are designated as protected areas. In contrast, only 1.18% of ABNJ, which makes up the remaining 61% of the global ocean, has been established as protected areas. At present, international discussions are underway to establish ways of simplifying the process to create MPAs in ABNJ. For more information on this, please see the DOALOS website.
key-39-blue.name: Marine protected area in KM2

key-45-blue.def: Fish stock status is the percentage of a country’s total catch that comes from overexploited or collapsed stocks, considering all fish stocks within a country’s exclusive economic zone (EEZs). Because continued and increased stock exploitation leads to smaller catches, this indicator sheds light on the impact of a fishing practices within its EEZs. A score of 100 indicates that none a country's fish catch come from stocks that are overexploited or collapsed, and a score of 0 indicates worst performance.
key-45-blue.name: Fish Stock Status EPI 10-year Change

key-46-blue.def: The total contribution of travel and tourism to GDP reflects GDP generated directly by the travel and tourism sector plus its indirect and induced impacts.
key-46-blue.name: Inernational Tourism Revenue as a % of GDP

key-EN.FSH.THRD.NO-blue.def: Fish species are based on Froese, R. and Pauly, D. (eds). 2008. Threatened species are the number of species classified by the IUCN as endangered, vulnerable, rare, indeterminate, out of danger, or insufficiently known.
key-EN.FSH.THRD.NO-blue.name: Fish species, threatened
key-EN.FSH.THRD.NO-blue.source: Froese, R. and Pauly, D. (eds). 2008. FishBase database, www.fishbase.org.
key-EN.FSH.THRD.NO-blue.dataset: Froese, R. and Pauly, D. (eds). 2008. FishBase database, www.fishbase.org.

key-ER.FSH.CAPT.MT-blue.def: Capture fisheries production measures the volume of fish catches landed by a country for all commercial, industrial, recreational and subsistence purposes.
key-ER.FSH.CAPT.MT-blue.name: Fishery production, capture and aquaculture (metric tons)

key-ER.MRN.PTMR.ZS-blue.def: Marine protected areas are areas of intertidal or subtidal terrain--and overlying water and associated flora and fauna and historical and cultural features--that have been reserved by law or other effective means to protect part or all of the enclosed environment.
key-ER.MRN.PTMR.ZS-blue.name: Marine protected areas (% of EEZ)
key-ER.MRN.PTMR.ZS-blue.source: World Database on Protected Areas (WDPA) where the compilation and management is carried out by United Nations Environment World Conservation Monitoring Centre (UNEP-WCMC) in collaboration with governments, non-governmental organizations, academia and industry. The data is available online through the Protected Planet website (https://www.protectedplanet.net/).
key-ER.MRN.PTMR.ZS-blue.dataset: World Database on Protected Areas (WDPA) where the compilation and management is carried out by United Nations Environment World Conservation Monitoring Centre (UNEP-WCMC) in collaboration with governments, non-governmental organizations, academia and industry. The data is available online through the Protected Planet website (https://www.protectedplanet.net/).

key-IS.SHP.GOOD.TU-blue.def: Port container traffic measures the flow of containers from land to sea transport modes., and vice versa, in twenty-foot equivalent units (TEUs), a standard-size container. Data refer to coastal shipping as well as international journeys. Transshipment traffic is counted as two lifts at the intermediate port (once to off-load and again as an outbound lift) and includes empty units.
key-IS.SHP.GOOD.TU-blue.name: Container Port Traffic (TEU)

key-SL.TLF.ACTI.ZS-blue.def: Labor force participation rate is the proportion of the population ages 15-64 that is economically active: all people who supply labor for the production of goods and services during a specified period.
key-SL.TLF.ACTI.ZS-blue.name: Labor force participation rate, total (% of total population ages 15-64)
key-SL.TLF.ACTI.ZS-blue.source: International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT database. Data retrieved on June 15, 2021.
key-SL.TLF.ACTI.ZS-blue.dataset: International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT database. Data retrieved on June 15, 2021.

key-epi-FSS-blue.def: Fish stock status evaluates the percentage of a country’s total catch that comes from overexploited or collapsed stocks, considering all fish stocks within a country’s EEZs. Because continued and increased stock exploitation leads to smaller catches, this indicator sheds light on the impact of a country’s fishing practices.
key-epi-FSS-blue.name: Fish Stock Status Environmental Performance Index

key-ohi-index-score-blue.def:
The Ocean Health Index is a decision-making tool and framework for conserving the human-ocean ecosystem because people need a healthy ocean. The Index is the first assessment tool that scientifically measures key elements from all dimensions of the ocean’s health — biological, physical, economic and social — to guide decision makers toward the sustainable use of the ocean.
Final OHI score that takes into account current status and predicted future status.
key-ohi-index-score-blue.name: Ocean Health Index

key-ports-blue.def: Total fisheries production measures the volume of aquatic species caught by a country for all commercial, industrial, recreational and subsistence purposes. The harvest from mariculture, aquaculture and other kinds of fish farming is also included.
key-ports-blue.name: Number of ports
